                  </persName>
            , I searched the prisoner, I found the duplicate of a watch which this gentleman pledged for a friend, the prisoner said he had pawned the spoons in Norfolk street.</p>
               <p>MR. RAY. I am a pawnbroker, I live in Norfolk Street, Middlesex Hospital. On the 1st of August, I took in 2 spoons of the prisoner, on the 2d, I took a pair of sugar tongs and four spoons for one pound.</p>
               <p>The prisoner said nothing in his defence, called three witnesses who gave him a good character.</p>
